commentTextItems.html: and it's flicked behind square leg for a couple. Ireland win by 7 wickets.

commentPostTextItems.html: So a comfortable win for Ireland with the skipper O'Brien bringing them home.
The win was set up though by a brilliant bowling performance from Craig Young who took 5 wickets.
So Ireland take a 1-0 lead in the three match series with the next game here on Wednesday.
Do have a read of Ryan Bailey's report which will be up soon but from Conor Hayes in Malahide it's goodbye.

commentTextItems.html: turned through a vacant mid wicket region
and he went for the win, inside edge onto the pads was all he got though
hit hard in the air down to long-off, another blow like that will win it
turned out to deep mid wicket
play and a miss outside the off stump
hit hard to mid-on
pushed to the man at cover
turned in front of square for a single this time
and smacked behind square leg to bring up his fifty, his first in 8 innings for Ireland
goes fine off the pads and the keeper allows it through
driven towards mid-on
quick single taken to backward point
big heave but it's edged down to the third man boundary
turned very fine and the fielder down there can't prevent another boundary
defended back to the bowler
pushed through the covers and the sweeper fields
misses with the cut shot
flicked behind square for a single
cracking cover drive which races away to the rope, great shot

milestones.description: Kevin O'Brien has scored 11 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Porterfield's record
Poynter has broken the record for most dismissals in an innings (4) in ODIs for IRE, going past Niall O'Brien's 3
Josh Davey has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for SCOT, going past Gordon Goudie's record

stories.title: Young's debut five-for sets up victory
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Scotland, 1st ODI, Malahide
stories.seoTitle: Craig Young's debut five-for sets up victory
stories.summary: Craig Young, the fast bowler released by Sussex twelve months ago, chose a good moment to become just the ninth player to take a five-wicket haul on ODI debut as he stole a march in the race to make the plane for Australia and New Zealand
